# asio v0.4.0

# setup

Recommendation : Unzip asio folder to /usr/share

# deployment

  /path/to/asio/bin/asio.sh deploy <name> </path/to/config.ttl>

This command will create the <name> webapp directory, create appropriate soft links of library files
and copies configuration files, the web.xml and the given config.ttl . Some sanity checks are
included, for now asio.sh will refuse to overwrite an existing webapp.
####################################################################################################
IMPORTANT : asio.sh expects $CATALINA_HOME to be set to the base directory of the target tomcat
installation. If $CATALINA_HOME is not set, it will default to /usr/share/tomcat .
####################################################################################################

# undeployment

  /path/to/asio/bin/asio.sh undeploy <name>

This will _DELETE_ the <name> folder in $CATALINA_HOME/webapps . asio.sh will refuse to delete
web application folders without a .asio marker file.

# Notes

asio.sh attempts to discover its installation directory, even if it is invoked through a symlink. If
home directory resolution fails, the $ASIO_HOME variable may be set manually, pointing to the
asio folder.
